01:01:49.298 --> 01:01:52.918
based on any amount of time points testing positive being counted towards

1040
01:01:52.928 --> 01:01:56.898
detection for that patient, and that risks overstating

1041
01:01:56.918 --> 01:01:58.178
ability to detect MRD.

1042
01:01:59.258 --> 01:02:03.158
We should be focused on landmark sensitivity, which is what needs

1043
01:02:03.198 --> 01:02:03.758
improvement.

1044
01:02:04.998 --> 01:02:08.678
And we also need to be careful as assays get closer to the clinic

1045
01:02:09.318 --> 01:02:12.778
and physicians are acting on the results of tests

1046
01:02:13.218 --> 01:02:16.838
just to realize the limitations of existing studies, where at

1047
01:02:16.898 --> 01:02:20.518
times we find studies could be enriched for higher stages or grades or early

1048
01:02:20.598 --> 01:02:24.218
relapses or conclusions drawn from limited number of patients who

1049
01:02:24.258 --> 01:02:27.748
