1055
01:02:45.598 --> 01:02:49.338
under what circumstances, and how this will vary in real patient samples.

1056
01:02:49.398 --> 01:02:52.768
So let's remember, these are highly personalized

1057
01:02:52.858 --> 01:02:56.478
assays for heterogeneous markers in individuals whose

1058
01:02:56.538 --> 01:02:58.158
cell-free DNA yields vary.

1059
01:02:59.878 --> 01:03:03.498
We should be using LoD95. This is the lowest

1060
01:03:03.538 --> 01:03:07.358
ctDNA level in blood that can be detected with 95%

1061
01:03:07.378 --> 01:03:11.018
likelihood, recognizing it varies per sample and

1062
01:03:11.078 --> 01:03:13.298
