1071
01:03:44.758 --> 01:03:48.678
number of molecules required for detection is greater than

1072
01:03:48.698 --> 01:03:52.598
or equal to 95%, given the amount of cell-free DNA

1073
01:03:52.638 --> 01:03:56.138
that's been sampled, or even better yet, that's been sequenced.

1074
01:03:56.178 --> 01:03:58.368
And it's super easy to predict with a binomial model.

1075
01:04:00.138 --> 01:04:03.328
For MRD, we've heard about breadth and depth and how that affects limit of

1076
01:04:03.338 --> 01:04:06.058
detection. And I just want to unpack that a little further.

1077
01:04:07.308 --> 01:04:11.198
If we have a test that assays, say, 100 mutations in 10 nanograms

