1089
01:04:47.538 --> 01:04:50.138
if the background error rate is not below one part per million,

1090
01:04:51.198 --> 01:04:53.918
you won't be able to resolve ctDNA at one part per million.

1091
01:04:54.998 --> 01:04:58.638
And with advances in error-corrected sequencing, this is increasingly becoming the

1092
01:04:58.658 --> 01:05:02.138
biological mutation frequency, which varies by mutation

1093
01:05:02.198 --> 01:05:05.598
context and can be as low as 10 to the minus six all the way down to 10 to the

