1095
01:05:09.238 --> 01:05:12.108
Now, there's a lot of excitement and promise for multi-omic approaches and

1096
01:05:12.138 --> 01:05:15.538
multi-analyte approaches, and I believe these will improve detection,

1097
01:05:16.238 --> 01:05:19.358
but where they're going to be most useful is in the intermediate range, not the

1098
01:05:19.418 --> 01:05:23.278
ultra-low ctDNA levels, just because the background errors are

1099
01:05:23.318 --> 01:05:26.818
higher, and it's just not possible to leverage those

1100
01:05:26.878 --> 01:05:30.038
to overcome these detection challenges.

1101
01:05:32.858 --> 01:05:36.578
Now, there are multiple technical and biological constraints then on MRD

1102
01:05:36.588 --> 01:05:37.108
detection.

